<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 04 at 11:33AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE RISK EXPECTED THIS AFTERNOON DUE TO LOW RELATIVE
HUMIDITY...
The combination of low relative humidity and ongoing drought
conditions will lead to an elevated fire risk this afternoon.
Relative humidity will drop into the 20s this afternoon with
generally light west and southwest winds between 5 and 10 mph.
While frequent gusts are not expected, winds could gust upwards of
15 mph.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn today. Use extreme caution when burning as fires may
get out of hand quickly in these conditions.</description>
